"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-08-Kenyan-marathon-runner-seeks-Olympic-gold-1vSY3izh14s-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Dan Williams  Copied  One of the most highly anticipated events at Paris 2024 is the marathon which begins at 2 a.m. ET on Aug. 10. In the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s event, Kenya\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Kelvin Kiptum was expected to feature in the medals after breaking the world marathon record in Chicago in 2023. But those dreams ended when Kiptum was tragically killed in a car crash in February 2024.  Benson Kipruto who came second to Kiptum in Chicago, says that both he and fellow Kenyan, defending Olympic champion Eliud Kipchoge, will do whatever it takes to win gold for Kenya and honor Kiptum.  Kipruto has been speaking with CGTN\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Dan Williams.  For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"